The '''Initiative for Peace and Human Rights''' ({{lang-de|Initiative für Frieden und Menschenrechte}}) was the oldest opposition group in [[East Germany]]. It was founded at the beginning of 1986 and was independent of the churches and state. In February 1990 it merged with [[New Forum]] and [[Democracy Now (East Germany)|Democracy Now]] to form [[Alliance 90]].
People involved in the Initiative for Peace and Human Rights included [[Bärbel Bohley]], [[Ulrike Poppe]], [[Martin Böttger]] and [[Ibrahim Böhme]].
