{{Infobox criminal | name = Joseph Paul Jernigan | image_name = Booking photograph of Joseph Paul Jernigan.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1954|1|31}} | birth_place = [[Geneva, Illinois]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1993|8|5|1954|1|31}} | death_place = [[Huntsville, Texas]] | conviction = Murder | conviction_penalty = Death by [[lethal injection]] | conviction_status = Executed }}
'''Joseph Paul Jernigan''' (January 31, 1954 – August 5, 1993) was a [[Texas]] murderer who was [[execution|executed]] by [[lethal injection]] at 12:31&nbsp;a.m.
In 1981, Jernigan was found guilty of "cold-blooded murder" and [[death penalty|sentenced to death]] for killing Edward Hale, a 75-year-old homeowner who discovered Jernigan and an accomplice as they were burglarizing his home.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Johnston|first1=Jessica|title=The American Body in Context: An Anthology|date=2001|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|pages=241–255|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iIWcRAAtxvcC&pg=PA241&lpg=PA241&dq=Joseph+Paul+Jernigan&source=bl&ots=0lF9x4SReB&sig=nAlIutlPymxVv8689vzWetxzzMA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwju-IrwpKTUAhUIxxQKHV_ZAHA4ChDoAQhDMAk#v=onepage&q=Joseph%20Paul%20Jernigan&f=false|accessdate=4 June 2017}}</ref> Jernigan spent 12 years in prison before his final plea for [[clemency]] was denied. At the prompting of a prison chaplain, he agreed to donate his body for scientific research or medical use. His cadaver was sectioned and photographed for the [[Visible Human Project]] and the [[University of Colorado School of Medicine]] by Dr. Vic Spitzer and associates.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Garling|first1=Caleb|title=Killer’s Corpse Lives Again in Ghostly Time-Lapse Photos|url=https://www.wired.com/2011/04/project-12-31/|website=Wired|accessdate=4 June 2017}}</ref> He is the subject of an [[HBO]] documentary ''Virtual Corpse'' and also appeared on the [[United Kingdom|British]] [[video game]] TV series, [[GamesMaster]]'s gore special.
