{{about|the book|the television show|Le Invasioni Barbariche}}
'''Le Invasioni Barbariche in Italia''' is Professor [[Pasquale Villari]]'s popular account of the barbarian invasions of the Roman Empire from the [[Nerva–Antonine dynasty#Antonine dynasty|Antonines]] to the coronation of [[Charlemagne]] in 800 A.D. as Holy Roman Emperor. The book was first published in 1901 by [[Hoepli|Ulrico Hoepli]] in Milan.<ref name=Invasioni>{{cite book|author=Villari, Pasquale|title=Le invasioni barbariche in Italia|year=1901|url=https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000351979}}</ref>

The book, with 3 maps and about 500 pages,<ref name=Invasioni/> was intended to be easy to read and appealing to the general reader of Italian. Hoepli published the second, third and fourth editions in 1905, 1920 and 1928. In the book, Villari's main focus is on the Teutonic invasions of the 3rd through 6th centuries A.D.

In 1902 Fisher Unvwin published a 2-volume translation (''The Barbarian Invasions of Italy'') by [[Linda White Mazini Villari|Linda Villari]], the wife of Pasquale Villari.<ref>{{cite book|author=Villari, Pasquale|translator=Villari, Linda|title=The Barbarian Invasions of Italy|year=1902|publisher=T. Fisher Unvwin|url=https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/005919523}}</ref>

{{blockquote|Madame Villari's translation is verbally as accurate as might have been expected; but somehow it lacks the attractiveness of the original.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Review of ''Le Invasioni Barbariche in Italia'' & ''The Barbarian Invasions of Italy''|journal=The Athenæum|date=23 August 1902|issue=no. 3904|pages=241–242|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=iau.31858029268129;view=1up;seq=255}}</ref>}}

{{blockquote|The figures of the chief actors in this strife of centuries—Alaric, Attila, Genseric, Theodoric, Justinian, Belisarius, Alboin—are well and forcibly drawn by Professor Villari.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Review of ''The Barbarian Invasions of Italy''|date=31 May 1902|journal=The Spectator|pages=256–257|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xYRAAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA256}}</ref>}}

