{{Infobox award | name = The National German Sustainability Award | current_awards = | image = | caption = | description = | presenter = | country = Germany | year = 2008 | website = {{URL|www.nachhaltigkeitspreis.de}} }}
The German Sustainability Award was established in 2008 to encourage the acceptance of social and ecological responsibility and to identify role models in this area. The award is endorsed by the [[German Federal Government]], local and business associations as well as numerous NGOs, among them [[UNESCO]] and [[UNICEF]]. The awards are presented to cities, companies and individuals promoting the idea of a sustainable society by Federal Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]] or other members of her cabinet.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nachhaltigkeitspreis.de/sonstige/english-summary/|title=English Summary - Deutscher Nachhaltigkeitspreis |accessdate=2015-11-18}}</ref> Responsible for the award is the foundation Deutscher Nachhaltigkeitspreis e.V.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nachhaltigkeitspreis.de/sonstige/stiftung/|title=Foundation Deutscher Nachhaltigkeitspreis e.V|accessdate=2016-06-29}}</ref>
==Awards== The German Sustainability Award includes the categories companies, products, municipalities (since 2012), research (since 2012), building (since 2013) and next economy (since 2016). Each category includes more than one award, for example includes die categories companies award for [[Small and medium-sized enterprises|SMEs]], medium-big and big companies.
